{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}}, A man’s face, with an eye exaggerated, derived from {{zh-l|*𦣻}}. The horizontal stroke was added later. Unrelated to {{zh-l|*自}}.

[[#Etymology 2|Etymology 2]]: {{Han simp|麵|f=麥|t=&nbsp;}} as adopted by the ''Chinese Character Simplification Scheme'' ({{lw|zh|pref=《|s:漢字簡化方案|漢字簡化方案|suf=》}}) in 1956.

