From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*sV-merl|t=face}}; cognate with {{cog|lus|hmêl||face}}, {{cog|kac|man||face}}. {{och-l|偭|id=1|to turn; to violate}} is probably cognate ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}), perhaps its [[endoactive]] ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

